description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced Nurse with the passion for Haematology?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have what it takes to join the team in developing the service for the future by being forward thinking, innovative and committed to the delivery of high quality care?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will assist in the delivery of a high quality Haematology service provided by nurse specialists. They will be responsible for the provision of nurse led outpatient services, in-patient and day case care for this client group. In addition the post holder will contribute to service development through education, research and audit. They will play a key role within the multi-disciplinary team in order to ensure a seamless, coordinated and timely approach to care. They will be expected to participate and develop nurse led clinics, maintain advice lines, give advice and implement care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Being committed to leading by example, encouraging and empowering the team is essential in ensuring the Trusts core values and beliefs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited from suitably experienced Clinical Nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note this position requires a Disclosure Barring Service check (DBS) formerly CRB. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
